  "prompt": "Is there a website where I can watch Broadway musical videos for free?",
  "response": "While there are several platforms where you can watch Broadway performances, free access is often limited due to copyright restrictions. However, here are a few options where you might find some free content:\n\n1. **YouTube**: Many clips, performances, and even full shows may be available. Some official theater channels and users post content related to Broadway performances.\n\n2. **Theater Companies**: Some theater companies occasionally release videos of their productions for promotional purposes. It\u2019s worth checking the official websites or social media pages of specific theaters.\n\n3. **PBS**: PBS often broadcasts performances of Broadway shows and may have their specials available for streaming online.\n\n4. **BroadwayHD**: This is a subscription service, but it sometimes offers free trials or promotional content that allows you to watch some shows for free for a limited time.\n\n5. **Library Services**: Check if your local library provides access to streaming services like Kanopy, which sometimes includes performances of theatrical productions.\n\nRemember to respect copyright laws and seek out authorized content.",
